            "description": "<div><div class=\"sc-drlTmn ixsurz\"><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Moodys (NYSE:<a class=\"ticker\" href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/quote/MCO\" target=\"_blank\">MCO</a>) has outperformed the market over the past 10 years by 4.47% on an annualized basis producing an average annual return of 17.2%. Currently, Moodys has a market capitalization of $86.61 billion. </p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><strong>Buying $100 In MCO:</strong> If an investor had bought $100 of MCO stock 10 years ago, it would be worth <strong>$492.10</strong> today based on a price of $485.51 for MCO at the time of writing.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><h3 class=\"block core-block\">Moodys's Performance Over Last 10 Years</h3><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-bOyZFT fVaRvi core-image flex items-center justify-center\"><span style=\"background:none;border:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:inline-block;height:initial;margin:0;opacity:1;overflow:hidden;padding:0;width:initial;position:relative;max-width:100%\"><span style=\"background:none;border:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:block;height:initial;margin:0;opacity:1;padding:0;width:initial;max-width:100%\"><img alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMTUwMCIgaGVpZ2h0PSI4MDAiIHhtbG5zPSJodHRwOi8vd3d3LnczLm9yZy8yMDAwL3N2ZyIgdmVyc2lvbj0iMS4xIi8+\" style=\"background:none;border:0;display:block;height:initial;margin:0;max-width:100%;opacity:1;padding:0;width:initial\"/></span><img alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"800\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" style=\"border:none;bottom:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:block;height:0;left:0;margin:auto;max-height:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;min-width:100%;padding:0;position:absolute;right:0;top:0;width:0;object-fit:contain\" width=\"1500\"/><noscript><img alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"low\" height=\"800\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 1500px, (min-width: 800px) 1500px\" src=\"https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1765494023_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=3840\" srcset=\"https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1765494023_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=1920 1x, https://www.benzinga.com/files/images/story/2025/1765494023_0.png?optimize=medium&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp&amp;width=3840 2x\" style=\"border:none;bottom:0;box-sizing:border-box;display:block;height:0;left:0;margin:auto;max-height:100%;max-width:100%;min-height:100%;min-width:100%;padding:0;position:absolute;right:0;top:0;width:0;object-fit:contain\" width=\"1500\"/></noscript></span></div><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Finally -- what's the point of all this? The key insight to take from this article is to note how much of a difference compounded returns can make in your cash growth over a period of time.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><em>This article was generated by Benzinga's automated content engine and reviewed by an editor.</em></p><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-iDItIC dKIoki\"></div><!--/$--></div></div>",
